IRS990.Desc: EXP PROVIDES WORK-BASED LEARNING EXPERIENCES TO HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS ACROSS 19 PATHWAYS AT 13 HIGH SCHOOLS THROUGHOUT SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA. THE PROGRAMS ARE AVAILABLE TO OVER 6,350 STUDENTS EACH SCHOOL YEAR. EXP PARTNERS WITH LOCAL INDUSTRIES AND HIGH SCHOOLS TO DELIVER INNOVATIVE, CAREER-BASED CURRICULUM THAT INSPIRES STUDENTS TO EXPLORE HIGH-SKILL, HIGH-GROWTH CAREER OPPORTUNITIES.IN ADDITION, EXP ENGAGES MORE THAN 400 INDUSTRY LEADERS AS BOARD MEMBERS, SPEAKERS, MENTORS, AND INTERNSHIP PROVIDERS TO PROVIDE SUPPORT AND RESOURCES TO EDUCATORS, HELPING TO INTEGRATE WORK-READINESS INTO THE CLASSROOM.

OtherAssetsOrgGrp.Desc: INVESTMENT IN FUNDS HELD BY OTHERS

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Grantmaker's Description of How Grants are Used
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS A SCHOLARSHIPS AND GRANTS COMMITTEE MADE UP OF MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION'S INDEPENDENT BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE COMMITTEE REVIEWS AND APPROVES ALL SCHOLARSHIPS AND GRANTS PAID TO INDIVIDUALS. SCHOLARSHIPS AND GRANTS ARE AWARDED TO INDIVIDUALS FOR EDUCATIONAL EXPENSES INCLUDING TUITION, BOOKS, SUPPLIES AND OTHER RELATED EDUCATIONAL EXPENSES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY MANAGEMENT BEFORE THE TAX RETURN IS FILED WITH THE IRS. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD AND THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS RECEIVE AND REVIEW A COPY OF THE TAX RETURN PRIOR TO FILING WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION REQUIRES ITS BOARD MEMBERS AND OFFICERS TO COMPLETE AN ANNUAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST QUESTIONNAIRE TO DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS. THE CEO REVIEWS EACH QUESTIONNAIRE AND FOLLOWS UP IF MORE INFORMATION IS NECESSARY TO DETERMINE PROPER DISCLOSURE FOR THE FORM 990. ANY BOARD MEMBER WITH A CONFLICT WILL ABSTAIN FROM VOTING ON ISSUES RELATED TO THAT CONFLICT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATIONS EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS CONVENES AN INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION COMMITTEE TO REVIEW AND APPROVE THE COMPENSATION PACKAGE OF THE ORGANIZATIONS TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL (CEO). IN DETERMINING THE COMPENSATION FOR THE TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL, THE COMMITTEE UTILIZES COMPARABILITY TO SUPPORT ITS DECISION MAKING PROCESS. THE COMMITTEE ADEQUATELY DOCUMENTS ITS COMPENSATION DETERMINATIONS AND DELIBERATIONS REGARDING COMPENSATION IN THE MINUTES ON A TIMELY BASIS. THE PROCESS FOR REVIEWING THE COMPENSATION OF THE ORGANIZATIONS TOP MANAGEMENT PROFESSIONAL IS UNDERTAKEN ON AN ANNUAL BASIS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATIONS EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEWS AND APPROVES THE RECOMMENDATIONS OF THE TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL (CEO) FOR THE COMPENSATION PACKAGES OF OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES AS PART OF THE OVERALL BUDGETING PROCESS. IN DETERMINING THE COMPENSATION OF OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES, THE CEO UTILIZES COMPARABILITY TO SUPPORT HER RECOMMENDATIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, POLICIES AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON FORMAL REQUEST.
